@node "install" "Installation"


  @{b}AmiHunter.amirx Installation@{ub}

  AmiHunter should have been installed by Kąą's installation, but I'll tell
  You where things are and go....:)

  AmiHunter.amirx - amirc/rexx/

  All the required libs in LIBS: or libs: path

  Zed_HTTP moved to C:


  @{b}AmiHunter.amirx Alaises@{ub}

      The following Alaises are part of the Kąą Alaises Plugin.

     Find  = /rx Amihunter find %p   
     Get   = /rx Amihunter get  %p 
     CSend = /rx AmiHunter Csend %p       
     USend = /rx Amihunter Usend %p     
     VRead = /rx Amihunter vread %p

@{b}Config@{ub}

     Your default download dir needs to be configured in the script
     load into a text editor and change to your download dir.

     Also config if you wish .readme's to be downloaded when you 
     download the file.

     Also config if you wish .readme's to be deleted after you 
     view them using the Vread option.

     See @{"How to Use" link "usage"} for Usage......
@endnode
@node "usage" "Using AmiHunter"

 @{b}Find@{ub}

   /find [EXACT] <"substring"|"sub strings">                 
                 [-w<width>] [-m<items>] [-s<site.number>] 

   Examples:                                                           
                                                                       
   /find AMSD                                                          
                                                                       
 «AmiHunter» Finding: amsd, width 100, maxlength 20,                   
             Site: ftp.uni-paderborn.de.                               
                                                                       
 «AmiHunter» 1. dcamsd21.lha   comm/tcp    50K Aminet Mini Searcher Downloader GUI/ Mini  
 «AmiHunter» 2. DreamsDark.lha mods/melom 287K Dreams of Dark (film/orch) 
 «AmiHunter» 3. dreamsdz.lha   mods/xm    572K Slow xm by Vogue        
                                                                       
 /csend 2,3 -- Will send files 2,3 to current channel              
                                                                       
 /usend <%U|nick> 2,3 -- will send text 2,3,4 to nick                     
         %U - will get select nick from users list                     
                                                                       
 /get 2,3,4 will download files 2,3,4                                  
  Zed_Httpget gui will open of WORKBENCH and show the progress of the file          
  Closing the GUI will abort the download                              

 /vread 2
  Will download the readme to T: and use mulitview to read the readme.

 Other Examples:                                                       
                                                                       
 /find "irc client"       - Searches for anything with "irc" AND "client"                     
 /find exact "irc client" - Searches for anything with "irc client" exactly
 /find amsd -m5           - Shows 5 lines of output                    
 /find amsd -w120         - Truncates output to 120 characters         
 /find amsd -w60 -m10     - Shows up to 10 lines truncating to 60 width
 /find "comm/net irc "    - Will search in comm/net (the directory)    
 /find amsd -s4           - Will uses site.4 in the site list          
                                                                       
 Tips:                                                                 
                                                                       
 o  If you search for more than one keyword you MUST put it in quotes. 
 o  Quotes must be " quotes, not ' quotes.                             
 o  - options MUST be the last options on the line.                    

@endnode
